Additional Markets


 


	Mitchell Metal Products

	Excellence from start to finish is more than a slogan at Mitchell Metal Products. It is the cornerstone upon which our Mission to meet and exceed our customers’ expectations with products of highest value, delivered on time in an environment that fosters employee and company growth and success is built.

	Every phase of manufacturing from product design and creation of tooling solutions to progressive metal stamping and secondary metal forming operations to finishing in our electro zinc plating lines is considered vital to our commitment to excellence. Whether you require simple progressively stamped metal parts or complex subassemblies, we stand ready to see your project through from initial design through finishing on our zinc plating lines or to your custom-specified finish.

	Mitchell Metal Products offers automated progressive metal stamping in press capacity ranging from 2 ½ tons through 400 tons. Our metal stamping capability is complimented by our wide range of nearly unmatched secondary metal forming capabilities including secondary press forming, press brake forming, robotic welding, resistance welding, tapping, riveting, orbital riveting, metal de-burring, barrel and rack line zinc plating. Proprietary MMP-iTool  insert tooling allows us to provide you with low upfront tooling options at hard-tooled piece part prices.





					Industries Served

























	Tooling Solutions

	Tooling solutions are provided economically by our in-house tool department. Our tooling department contains a number of work centers featuring the latest in metal machining technology. Our large bed 4 Axis CNC machining center makes quick work of large tooling blocks and die sets. It is complimented by our Mitsubishi Wire EDM. Tooling blocks are economically ground on our large automated surface grinder. A number of lathes, end mills, heat treating furnaces and additional surface grinders complete our tooling department allowing us to economically offer tooling solutions for your metal stamping and subassembly requirements.

Contact us today with your design challenges and allow our dedicated staff of expert metal stamping and forming designers to demonstrate our commitment to excellence from start to finish. 








